    "body": "I see, the issue here is that we're trying to resolve foundry config because the bn command also supports chain aliases.\r\n\r\nwe can make this a bit smarter though\r\n\r\ninstead of resolving the config:\r\nhttps://github.com/foundry-rs/foundry/blob/1c7bf46cdf267f06caba6e063329c6ce8f5c914a/crates/cast/bin/main.rs#L231-L231\r\n\r\nwe should check if URL argument is none (or a valid URL and __no__ alias) and return localhost or that URL parameter, or the flashbots URL if --flashbots and don't resolve the config",
